&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Clinical Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Opportunities available at Wharfedale Hospital, St James’s and Leeds General Infirmary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Please specify your preference of site within your supporting information. Failure to do so may affect your application being shortlisted.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Surgical Pre-assessment Service at Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust has an exciting opportunity for a Clinical Support Worker at LGI, SJUH Hospital and Wharfedale Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit a Clinical Support Worker (CSW) who will work as part of the Nursing and Admin team to provide patient care, Observations, and Support to patients and their relatives during their pre-assessment appointment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic team members who will assist in the smooth running of the department who possesses NVQ 2 in Health &amp; Social Care or equivalent.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Desirable skills, phlebotomy, ECG recording, and Administrative systems (PAS) but training will be provided for the right candidate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Come and join our team in Leeds and become part of ‘The Leeds Way’ sharing our vision and values. Our Trust is recognised for our staff engagement, great care and rated &lt;strong&gt;GOOD&lt;/strong&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust is one of the largest acute health providers in the UK and based in one of the fastest growing and vibrant cities in the north.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful candidates must hold a level 2 NVQ in health and social care or an equivalent healthcare related qualification and have experience of working in a health care setting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For all new starters to the Trust we have an award winning, structured Introduction to Professional Practice (IPP) Induction programme to prepare you for working at LTHT. Within the first three months of your role you will be required to complete the Cavendish Care Certificate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will take place virtually following COVID-19 guidelines.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal visits are encourage - to arrange please contact &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sister Karen Waterhouse at Leeds General Infirmary 0113 392 8026&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sister Ann-Marie Jones at St James’s Hospital 0113 206 6467&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Internal care support staff&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; currently employed by Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust, who wish to work in a different area, at the same AfC Band, job description and person specification should contact their Matron and employ the internal transfer process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;We may share information, as appropriate, that you have provided in your application form with external partners or other organisations help to facilitate your recruitment process.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
